  <section id="bio">
    <h2>About Vanessa</h2>
    <p>Welcome to Vanessa's Health Hub! I'm Vanessa, an incoming college freshman passionate about educating the general public on medical technology and healthcare innovation. My goal is to make complex medical advancements easy to understand and accessible to everyone. Through this blog, I share insights about how modern tools—from advanced imaging techniques to artificial intelligence—are transforming patient care, improving diagnosis, and shaping the future of medicine.</p>
    <p>As I begin my college journey, I’m excited to deepen my knowledge and share it here with readers who are curious about the rapidly evolving world of healthcare technology. Whether you’re a student, healthcare professional, or just interested in the latest medical trends, you’ll find thoughtful, research-backed articles and resources here.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="blog">
    <h2>Latest Blog Posts</h2>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#post-ai-imaging">The Rise of AI in Medical Imaging</a></li>
        <li><a href="#post-wearables">Wearable Health Tech: Monitoring Beyond the Clinic</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
    <div id="blog-posts">
      <article id="post-ai-imaging" class="post">
        <h3>The Rise of AI in Medical Imaging</h3>
        <time datetime="2025-07-01">July 1, 2025</time>
        <p>Artificial intelligence (AI) is revolutionizing medical imaging by assisting radiologists in detecting diseases faster and with greater accuracy. Advanced machine learning algorithms analyze X-rays, MRIs, and CT scans, identifying subtle patterns that might be missed by the human eye. This technology not only speeds up diagnosis but also reduces errors and enhances personalized treatment planning.</p>
        <p>For example, AI tools can help detect early signs of cancer, cardiovascular conditions, and neurological disorders by highlighting suspicious areas for closer review. Hospitals worldwide are increasingly adopting AI-powered imaging software, leading to improved patient outcomes and more efficient workflows.</p>
        <p>While AI holds tremendous promise, it’s important to balance technology with human expertise, ensuring ethical use, patient privacy, and rigorous validation of these tools. As AI continues to evolve, it will become an indispensable partner in the healthcare ecosystem.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="post-wearables" class="post">
        <h3>Wearable Health Tech: Monitoring Beyond the Clinic</h3>
        <time datetime="2025-06-15">June 15, 2025</time>
        <p>Wearable health technology—such as smartwatches, fitness trackers, and biosensors—is transforming how people manage their health outside traditional medical settings. These devices continuously monitor vital signs like heart rate, blood oxygen levels, sleep quality, and physical activity, providing real-time data that can help detect early warning signs of illness.</p>
        <p>For patients with chronic conditions like diabetes or hypertension, wearables offer a proactive approach by alerting users and healthcare providers to potential problems before they escalate. Additionally, these devices promote healthier lifestyles by motivating users to stay active and maintain better habits.</p>
        <p>Many wearables now integrate AI to offer personalized insights and coaching, adapting recommendations based on user behavior. While privacy and data security are ongoing concerns, wearable tech continues to expand the possibilities for patient-centered care and remote monitoring.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
